replies.body:
I personally think Veigar is fine for these reasons, and enjoy playing him for that sweet sweet sensation of nuking your opponent into the great beyond. His e is less powerful as an out of nowhere engage which is what riot intended, and the result is that lots of e's power is in preventing an enemy or enemies from achieving a goal. 'Oh, you want to dive me? Get past the ring of death.' 'Oh, you wanted to run down that jungle path? Burn flash or walk back towards me.' It's an effective trap; a cage meant to be dropped on your enemys when it's most inconvenient for them. When used beyond that then yeah, they can spam the dance emote within it's confines for all I care.

Aside from that it is true that veigar's kit lacks a lot of interaction, but being the iconic burst mage that he is is just where so much of his power is. To give him the w knock around skill or any changes like that would result in a nerf to his damage, something that defines him. I don't know about you, but nothing in my opinion is sweeter than one shoting the enemy mage with your ult. 

DELETE!{{champion:45}}
